      "fontFamily": 1,
      "text": "Event Sourcing\n    - A service can store the aggregated events locally to create a \"state\".\n    - Like we did with the catalog item created, catalog item retired - \n        - the *sum* of those gives us the current list of supported software.\n\n\nEvent sourcing is rad, but can cause a lot of duplications, weird errors, etc.\nAdds a lot of complexity to each API that needs that data.\nThis tends to happen in subdomains (and even bounded contexts)\n\ne.g. \"In the help desk platform, we have a lot of app (services) that need the list of current software\"\n    or \"We need a subset of the information about a customer, not all of it!\"\n\n\nCan create a \"shared store\" that has just the stuff you need (in the \"ubiquitous language\" of the platform,\nsub-domain)\n\nThis could be stored in a database, and accessible as an RPC API (using HTTP, whatever)\nOR it could be a stream of DOCUMENTS.\n    - this is an \"adapter\" or sometimes called an \"ACL\" (Anti-Corruption Layer)\n\n\nBest possible world:\n    - The service that owns shared data publishes documents with the *minimal* amount of data\npossible.\n\n\nDocuments\n\n    - Aggregates of a \"thing\" over time. \n\nCommands\n\n    - Not usually used across bounded contexts\n    - Like an event, but you have a single expected outcome.\n\n\n\n\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Event Sourcing\n    - A service can store the aggregated events locally to create a \"state\".\n    - Like we did with the catalog item created, catalog item retired - \n        - the *sum* of those gives us the current list of supported software.\n\n\nEvent sourcing is rad, but can cause a lot of duplications, weird errors, etc.\nAdds a lot of complexity to each API that needs that data.\nThis tends to happen in subdomains (and even bounded contexts)\n\ne.g. \"In the help desk platform, we have a lot of app (services) that need the list of current software\"\n    or \"We need a subset of the information about a customer, not all of it!\"\n\n\nCan create a \"shared store\" that has just the stuff you need (in the \"ubiquitous language\" of the platform,\nsub-domain)\n\nThis could be stored in a database, and accessible as an RPC API (using HTTP, whatever)\nOR it could be a stream of DOCUMENTS.\n    - this is an \"adapter\" or sometimes called an \"ACL\" (Anti-Corruption Layer)\n\n\nBest possible world:\n    - The service that owns shared data publishes documents with the *minimal* amount of data\npossible.\n\n\nDocuments\n\n    - Aggregates of a \"thing\" over time. \n\nCommands\n\n    - Not usually used across bounded contexts\n    - Like an event, but you have a single expected outcome.\n\n\n\n\n",
